                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d37">
                <head>No. 37.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Tree</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Bayard</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States.</hi>
                            <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Brussels</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1888-06-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">June</hi> 30, 1888</date>. (Received July
                        16.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 359.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: As the money coined and put in circulation by a
                    new state has, perhaps, a certain interest, I have ventured to send you to-day
                    by post, under a separate cover, specimens of the first moneys ever coined by
                    the Independent State of the Congo.</p>
                <p>The package contains specimens of pieces of a half franc, and of 1, 2, and 5
                    francs in silver, and of 1, 2, 5, and 10 centimes in copper. No gold pieces have
                    been coined as yet.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lambert Tree.</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
